message: /* History of the hypothesis */ this makes it clear that the opponents to the hypothesis are themselves a small group.

/* History of the hypothesis */ Two changes. First, the phrase 'mainstream scientists' is meaningless here. Second, the scepticism is Rex Daulton's alone. No evidence is provided that could warrant the more general 'scientific skepticism'.
/* Evidence */ Moved lines from 'evidence' that naturally belong in 'criticism'
/* YD impact hypothesis - are you going to replace the material you thought was in the wrong section */
This line was mistakenly in the 'evidence' section, when it clearly belonged in the 'criticism' section
/* See also */ updated links to wiki pages
/* Interpretation */ link to new wiki page on coherent catasrophism
Added most recent publications, which support the hypothesis. Also, called out the attempt at character assassination for what it is.
/* Interpretation */ Include the widely reported claims of Sweatman and Tsikritsis, published in a peer reviewed academic journal
/* See also */ added link to coherent catastrophism
